issue.title: Fix TimeUtilities thread number counting synchronization

labels.name: criu
labels.description: Used to track CRIU snapshot related work

repository.name: openj9
repository.description: Eclipse OpenJ9: A Java Virtual Machine for OpenJDK that's optimized for small footprint, fast start-up, and high throughput.   Builds on Eclipse OMR (https://github.com/eclipse/omr) and combines with the Extensions for OpenJDK for OpenJ9 repo.

issue.body:
Fix TimeUtilities thread number counting synchronization

Use `AtomicInteger` to update the thread number atomically.

closes https://github.com/eclipse-openj9/openj9/issues/20464

Signed-off-by: Jason Feng <fengj@ca.ibm.com>

issue.title: JFR can invoke VM.setJFRRecordingFileName() before VM.startJFR()

repository.name: openj9
repository.description: Eclipse OpenJ9: A Java Virtual Machine for OpenJDK that's optimized for small footprint, fast start-up, and high throughput.   Builds on Eclipse OMR (https://github.com/eclipse/omr) and combines with the Extensions for OpenJDK for OpenJ9 repo.

issue.body:
JFR can invoke `VM.setJFRRecordingFileName()` before `VM.startJFR()`

Allow `VM.setJFRRecordingFileName()` to be invoked before `VM.startJFR()`;
Ignore the changing of the recording filename within the commands `JFR.dump` and `JFR.stop`.


Related to
* https://github.com/eclipse-openj9/openj9/issues/21069

Signed-off-by: Jason Feng <fengj@ca.ibm.com>
